                            'The King in the City of Life, dwelling in the mansions of royalty.  He is Eternal, his splendor rises and illuminates, He is without end, measure, and number.',
                            'He rejoices in joy without sorrow, and his entire kingdom rejoices with Him.  A (beautiful) picture, a grace and magnificence (is he), that there is no beauty that resembles him.',
                            'The Truth is who dwells in the heights above, the Lord of Greatness, the Lord of All Great Things.  No one can describe His power and that of all His worlds, nor his Shkinas in which he dwells, nor the Uthras and kings who dwell in them.',
                            'That High King of Light sits safely in his dwelling . He is higher than all beings, like the earth to its creatures.  He towers over all like the heavens over the mountains.  He shines more than all like a sun shines more than lamps.  He is brighter than all like the moon is brighter than the stars.',
                            'He is of qualities in which there is no defect.  Great crowns are placed upon him that his power and greatness are limitless.  He is not limited by number or account.',
                            'The sparks of his crown sparkle everywhere.  Rays of splendor, light, and glory emanate from His face and between the leaves of His wreath.  All Uthras and kings, indeed all worlds, stand in prayer and praise and praise that High King of Light.',
                            'Five mighty, great qualities emanate from Him.  The first is His light which rises upon them.  The second is His fragrance which blows upon them.  The third is His sweetness of voice, by which they rejoice.  The fourth is the speech of His mouth, by which He creates and begets them.  The fifth is the beauty of His form, which makes them grow like the fruit in the sun.',
                            'All Uthras opened their mouths, they praise that High King of Light and say unto him: Who shall praise You, who shall glorify You, who shall bless You, who shall honor You, who shall strengthen You?  If we should praise You with Your praises, Your praise is limitless.  If we should bless You with Your blessings, Your blessings are vast and endless.  If we are to cherish You according to Your majesty, Your majesty is immeasurable.  If we are to praise You according to Your depth, Your depth is unfathomable.  If we are to speak of Your power, Your splendor, and Your light, your splendor is too vast to speak of in words, Your light is too rich and great to speak and tell in words.',
                            'The blessing, grace, and majesty of the High King of Light blossom forth, come forth, and cannot be contained.  None can comprehend nor understand them except the life that is with You and the Uthras and messengers that stand before You.  All beings know not Your name.  The kings stand there and say to each other: “What is the name of the Great Light?”  They say: “There is no name like Its name, there is no one who calls It by Its name, no one who understands Its name.”',
                            'Hail the perfect ones who knew You with a pure heart, thought of You with a true mind, and believed in You with a clear conscience, who blessed You with a mouth which is all praise, who praised You with a sincere tongue, confessed You with believing lips, and said: “One is the Light King in his realm, there is none greater than Him, none who made war with Him.  There is none who can compare to His form, none who lifts up his eyes to see the crown on the head of that High King of Light without his own crown falling from his head.',
